3. TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

(From the comprehensive technical specifications document)

3.1 Cognitive Core (Zone 1)

Component Specification
AI Cluster 256x NVIDIA H100 GPUs, NVLink Switch, ~1 ExaFLOP
Quantum Computers 2x IBM Quantum System Two (1,500+ qubits), 1x Quantinuum H2
Neuromorphic Nodes 10x Intel Loihi 2 racks
Storage 50 PB all‑NVMe parallel file system, >1 TB/s
Network Backbone 400G/800G Ethernet, InfiniBand NDR, QKD links

3.2 Intelligent Learning System (Zone 3)

Component Specification
AI Tutor Custom LLM, >95% intent recognition, <300 ms latency
AR/VR Headsets Apple Vision Pro / Varjo XR‑4 (high‑end), Meta Quest Pro (general)
Spatial Engine Unreal Engine 5.4, cloud XR streaming

3.3 Autonomous Research Labs (Zone 2)

Component Specification
Mobile Robots 20x Boston Dynamics Spot with Stretch arm, 5 kg payload
Collaborative Arms 10x Universal Robots UR20e, ±0.05 mm precision
Quantum Lab Environment Dilution fridges <10 mK, vibration isolation, mu‑metal shielding

3.4 Energy Autonomous Campus (Zone 4)

Component Specification
Solar Generation 5 MW bifacial with trackers
Hydrogen System 2 MW PEM electrolyzer, 1,000 kg storage, 500 kW fuel cells
Magnetic Harvesting Roadway inductive coils, 10‑20 kW per lane
Microgrid Controller SEL RTAC with AI co‑processor, 5‑second optimization cycle

3.5 Campus Digital Twin

Component Specification
Platform NVIDIA Omniverse / AWS TwinMaker
Update Rate Real‑time (<50 ms) for dynamic elements
Geospatial Resolution 3 cm (drone photogrammetry)
BIM Level LOD 350

3.6 Sensor & Actuator Layer

Type Examples Protocols
Environmental PM, CO₂, VOC, light, acoustic (privacy‑filtered) MQTT
Structural Fiber Bragg gratings, accelerometers Modbus
Biometric Smart badges (UWB), edge‑based facial vectors MQTT/HTTPS
Actuators Lighting, HVAC, robot commands OPC‑UA, ROS 2

3.7 Cybersecurity & Governance

Component Specification
Zero Trust Micro‑segmentation, mTLS, continuous verification
Quantum‑Safe Crypto Lattice‑based encryption for long‑term data
Audit Trail Hyperledger Fabric blockchain
Explainability LIME/SHAP for all human‑impacting models

