4. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP

(From the implementation plan)

4.1 Phase 1: Foundation & Core (Months 0‑12)

· Construct Zone 1 shell, Tier IV data center
· Install fiber backbone across campus
· Deploy Kubernetes, Kafka, basic sensor mesh
· Deliverable: Secure, powered core with construction Digital Twin

4.2 Phase 2: Energy & Residential (Months 12‑24)

· Build Zones 4 and 5
· Install solar, hydrogen, microgrid controller
· Deploy smart home infrastructure
· Launch Energy Management System
· Deliverable: Net‑zero residential area with real‑time energy visibility

4.3 Phase 3: Learning & Intelligence (Months 24‑36)

· Build Zone 3
· Deploy smart classrooms, AR/VR, AI Tutor v1
· Integrate wearable engagement sensors
· Deliverable: First student cohort experiences AI‑personalized learning

4.4 Phase 4: Advanced Research (Months 36‑48)

· Build Zone 2
· Install quantum computers and neuromorphic nodes
· Deploy autonomous research assistants
· Implement full governance and Digital Twin
· Deliverable: Fully operational, self‑optimizing smart university

4.5 Risk Register

Risk Mitigation
Technology integration complexity Use system integrator, canonical data model
Data privacy concerns Opt‑in architecture, edge processing, consent management
Quantum vendor lock‑in Abstraction layer (Qiskit, Braket)
Cost overrun Phased approach, grid‑tie option
Skills gap Vendor training, hire AI campus architects

---

5. SYSTEM API SPECIFICATION V1.0

(Full API specification as previously detailed)

Base URL: https://api.quenne.edu/v1
Authentication: OAuth 2.0 (Bearer) or API key (X‑API‑Key)
Rate Limits: 1,000/hr (user), 10,000/hr (service)

5.1 Core Services Summary

Service Base Path Key Endpoints
Cognitive /cognitive POST /inference, GET /models
Learning /learning GET /students/{id}/progress, POST /tutor/sessions
Research /research POST /robots/{id}/commands, GET /experiments/{id}
Energy /energy GET /status, POST /policy
Residential /residential POST /devices/{id}/control, POST /mobility/book
Digital Twin /twin GET /assets/{id}, POST /simulations
Governance /governance GET /audit, GET /explain/{id}, POST /consent

5.2 Webhooks

Register at /webhooks to receive asynchronous events (e.g., energy.peak, robot.error, tutor.session.ended). Payloads signed with HMAC‑SHA256.

