10. APPENDICES

10.1 Glossary of Terms

· Digital Twin: A virtual representation of a physical system that is continuously updated and can simulate behavior.
· Cognitive Core: The central data center housing all AI, quantum, and HPC resources.
· Edge MDC: Micro Data Center located in each zone for low‑latency processing.
· Zero Trust: Security model where no entity is trusted by default, even inside the network.
· QKD: Quantum Key Distribution – use of quantum mechanics to securely distribute encryption keys.
· Neuromorphic Computing: Hardware that mimics neural structures for energy‑efficient AI.

10.2 Acronyms

Acronym Expansion
ACCS Autonomous Campus Control Software
